    "question_id" : 1842734,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>It's probably not a real solution, but now - in Java 8 - You can make this code look at least a little better using lambda expression.</p>\n\n<pre><code>final String x = \"somethingelse\";\nnew Thread(() -&gt; {\n        x.matches(\"something\");             \n    }\n).start();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And You could even do this in one line, still having it pretty readable.</p>\n\n<pre><code>new Thread(() -&gt; x.matches(\"something\")).start();\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 63162,
      "reputation" : 105842,
      "user_id" : 187141,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 82,
