    "answer_id" : 45007880,
    "question_id" : 1842734,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use <a href=\"http://static.javadoc.io/org.cactoos/cactoos/0.10/org/cactoos/func/AsyncFunc.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>AsyncFunc</code></a> from <a href=\"http://www.cactoos.org\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Cactoos</a>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>boolean matches = new AsyncFunc(\n  x -&gt; x.matches(\"something\")\n).apply(\"The text\").get();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>It will be executed at the background and the result will be available in <code>get()</code> as a <code>Future</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3150070,
      "reputation" : 10336,
      "user_id" : 2663692,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 32,
